beer.beer_description:
Esquire Magazine calls our 90 Minute IPA "perhaps the best IPA in America." An imperial IPA best savored from a snifter, 90 Minute has a great malt backbone that stands up to the extreme hopping rate.
90 Minute IPA was the first beer we continuously hopped, allowing for a pungent, but not crushing, hop flavor.

items.badge_description: Foolhardy quantities of hops. Check. Crushingly bitter? Not so much. Continual hopping - dosing with hops throughout the entire boil - delivers outrageously hoppy IPAs with balance. Check out our beers (continually hopped and otherwise) at dogfish.com. And don't forget to check in a 60 Minute IPA to unlock that badge!
Load up those hops, watch the IBU grow and drink it down! Now you’re all hopped up. The more bitter, the better. That's 60 different beers with an IBU of 65 or higher. Try 5 more for Level 13!

When a single isn’t enough, make it a double. Doubling the hops and malts in a recipe results in a higher ABV and can pack quite a boozey punch. That's 50 different beers with the style that contains Imperial / Double in its style name. Try 5 more for Level 11!
